race.comment: SPRING BRUMBY (4) was popular in betting last start but disappointed when 8 lengths away in fifth (23.85). Was in the money the start prior. Has ability and is a key runner. PYRENEES ACE (1) is a fast beginner who has shown good improvement at his last two starts, breaking through last time at this track over 390m. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Capable of going well again. UPTOWN SALLY (5) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by a head at Warrnambool in a handy 22.44 beating How Delightful. Strong form has emerged from her last run. Can make it back-to-back wins. MIDNIGHT IN SALE (3) won as favourite last time and is in the mix again.
